TITLE: Creating a Relational Virtual Field
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates a more complex virtual field that fetches related data. It defines an 'authorName' field on a Post list that retrieves the author's name by querying the related Author record.
SOURCE: https://github.com/keystonejs/keystone/blob/main/docs/content/docs/guides/virtual-fields.md#2025-04-13_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export default config({
  lists: {
    Post: list({
      fields: {
        content: text(),
        author: relationship({ ref: 'Author', many: false }),
        authorName: virtual({
          field: graphql.field({
            type: graphql.String,
            async resolve(item, args, context) {
              const { author } = await context.query.Post.findOne({
                where: { id: item.id.toString() },
                query: 'author { name }',
              });
              return author && author.name;
            },
          }),
        }),
      },
    }),
    Author: list({
      fields: {
        name: text({ validation: { isRequired: true } }),
      },
    }),
  },
});
```

