TITLE: Bypassing Access Control with context.sudo() in Keystone.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use context.sudo() to bypass access control in a custom GraphQL query. It checks if an email is in use without exposing other user data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/keystonejs/keystone/blob/main/docs/content/docs/guides/auth-and-access-control.md#2025-04-13_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const extendGraphqlSchema = graphQLSchemaExtension({
  typeDefs: `
    type Query {
      isEmailInUse(email: String!): Boolean!
    }`,
  resolvers: {
    Query: {
      isEmailInUse: async (root, { email }, context) => {
        const sudoContext = context.sudo();
        const emailCount = await sudoContext.db.User.count({
          where: {
            email: { equals: email, mode: 'insensitive' },
          },
        });
        return !!emailCount;
      },
    },
  },
});
```

