TITLE: Implementing Singleton Pattern for BaseProject in Keystone.js
DESCRIPTION: This code defines a BaseProject class with a static getInstance method to ensure only one instance is created. It includes methods for initialization and retrieval of configuration and keystone instance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/keystonejs/keystone/blob/main/examples/singleton/README.md#2025-04-13_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class BaseProject {
  static getInstance() {
    if (!BaseProject.instance) {
      BaseProject.instance = new BaseProject();
    }
    return BaseProject.instance;
  }

  constructor() {
    this.keystone = null;
    this.config = null;
  }

  async init(config) {
    this.config = config;
    this.keystone = new Keystone(config);
    await this.keystone.connect();
  }

  getKeystone() {
    return this.keystone;
  }

  getConfig() {
    return this.config;
  }
}

module.exports = BaseProject;
```

