TITLE: Using Context Functions for UI Configuration in Keystone 6
DESCRIPTION: Configuration functions that now accept a context argument, enabling dynamic UI behaviors based on the current request context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/keystonejs/keystone/blob/main/packages/core/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-13_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// List level UI configuration with context
list: {
  ui: {
    isHidden: ({ context }) => context.session?.data.role !== 'admin',
    hideCreate: ({ context }) => !context.session?.data.canCreateItems,
    hideDelete: ({ context }) => !context.session?.data.canDeleteItems,
    createView: {
      defaultFieldMode: ({ context }) => context.session ? 'edit' : 'hidden'
    },
    itemView: {
      defaultFieldMode: ({ context }) => context.session ? 'edit' : 'read'
    },
    listView: {
      defaultFieldMode: ({ context }) => context.session ? 'read' : 'hidden'
    }
  }
}

// Field level UI configuration with context
field: {
  ui: {
    createView: {
      fieldMode: ({ context }) => context.session?.data.canEdit ? 'edit' : 'hidden'
    },
    itemView: {
      fieldMode: ({ context }) => context.session?.data.canEdit ? 'edit' : 'read'
    },
    listView: {
      fieldMode: ({ context }) => context.session ? 'read' : 'hidden'
    }
  }
}
```

